The C/C++ Development Tooling (CDT) is a set of Eclipse plug-ins which
provide a fully featured C/C++ IDE. The main focus of the CDT is to support
the freely available open source compilers and tools, such as the
GNU Tools: GCC, GDB and Make.
The CDT is an official Eclipse Foundation project.
The CUTE Plug-in integrates the test framework
into the Eclipse CDT. The main features are:
auto register existing and new test functions
The gcov Feature for CUTE creates a build
configuration to get coverage data using
gcov and visualizes this information in the editor.
